webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Dahla’s seal north of the Åtvidaberg bears a long history. Mentioned for the first time in 1320, the estate has been held by a variety of genera, Boat, Sack, Fock and Adelswärd to name a few. At the time of the picture, the estate was owned by Gottfrid Johansson - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000633. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419923. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
